However, the increasing number of exciting and influential publications has primarily, if not exclusively, focused on the body in Western cultures. The various works produced by Asian scholars remain largely unknown to Western academic debates even though Asia is home to a host of rich body cultures and religions. The peoples of Asia have experienced colonization, decolonization, and now globalization, all of which make the ‘body in Asia’ a rewarding field of research. This unique volume brings together a number of scholars who work on East, Southeast and South Asia and presents original and cutting edge research on the body in various Asian cultures.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Nov 2022) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / General.2bisacsh1 aBautista, Julius, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrownell, Susan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDix, Monika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGainty, Denis, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHellman, Jörgen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aIshiguro, Junko, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLora-Wainwright, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNair, Santhosh Raghavan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPlanta, Mercedes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTurner, Bryan S., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTurner, Bryan S., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWichelen, Sonja van, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYangwen, Zheng, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators